claim.claim-text:
1. A recording apparatus, comprising:
a recording head, adapted to eject ink toward a recording medium which is transported in a first direction;
a first platen portion, adapted to support the recording medium;
a second platen portion, adapted to support the recording medium and disposed downstream from the first platen portion relative to the first direction so as to form a first gap located between the first platen portion and the second platen portion and opposing the recording head;
a third platen portion disposed downstream from the second platen portion relative to the first direction so as to form a second gap located between the second platen portion and the third platen portion and opposing the recording head; and
an ink absorbing member, adapted to absorb the ink ejected from the recording head, and located in the first gap and the second gap.
